http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/TS-official-to-coordinate-NITI-Aayog-survey/article14014725.ece

The State government has announced a nodal officer to coordinate with NITI Aayog on a nationwide survey being undertaken by the institution to assess the ease of doing business levels for manufacturing.The Commissioner/Director of Industries has been appointed as the nodal officer to coordinate with the Aayog “from time to time for smooth conduct of the survey,” a GO issued on Friday said.Start-ups would also be part of the survey, according to the Aayog. The objective of the exercise is to assess the regulatory environment and identify policy and regulatory hurdles faced by businesses in the States/UTs. A comprehensive analysis and report on State-level performance would be brought out.